			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well... if you're certain you don't need to read it, then don't.
<br />
<br />Acknowledging NMIs is not necessary.  The only practical reason I can think of for reading it, is if you're afraid 2005/2006 writes might get interrupted and you need to reset that latch.  Probably a good defensive programming practice, but there's no rule that says you have to do it.</div>

